below redshift 1.1 in 5.4 deg$^2$ have been\ndetected. The reliability of our method was examined through false detection\ntests, redshift uncertainty tests, and applications on the COSMOS data, giving\nfalse detection rates of 0.01 to 0.05 and recovery rate of 0.9 at high\nrichness. 3 X-ray clusters previously observed by $ROSAT$ and $Chandra$ were\nrecovered. The cluster galaxies show higher stellar mass and lower star\nformation rate (SFR) compared to the field galaxies in two-sample Z-tests.\nThese cluster candidates are useful for environmental studies of galaxy\nevolution and future astronomical surveys in the NEP, where $AKARI$ has\nperformed unique 9-band mid-infrared photometry for tens of thousands of\ngalaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 21 Jul 2021 11:12:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-08-25"}
